(337, 42, NULL, 0, 'Saniflo Sanicondens Best Pump', NULL, '<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(88, 104, 108); font-family: &quot;PT Serif&quot;, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 250);\">The Saniflo Sanicondens Best Pump was specially designed to dispose of the acidic condensate from usual condensing boilers. In can be easily installed and used with other equipment such as dehumidifiers and air conditioners. Although small in size — 28 x 180 x 122 mm, this powerful until will take the condensate from a boiler or other water-producing appliance and efficiently pump it into a drain. A versatile unit, the Saniflo Sanicondens Best Pump can either be wall or floor mounted. It is efficient in its pumping capabilities, pumping up to 342 litres per hour. It can also pump vertically up to 5 metres. If it is mounted vertically, it can pump up to 156 litres per hour. This unit will effectively get rid of condensate in an effective and quick manner.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(88, 104, 108); font-family: &quot;PT Serif&quot;, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 250);\">Please note: The dimensions shown here are of the unit only and do not allow for these additional space requirements as they may differ for each installation. It is the responsibility of the purchaser or installer to ensure that the Saniflo product selected will fit in the chosen place of installation with due allowance for pipework runs, electrical connections etc.</span><br></p>', 97, 95, '2.0618556701030926', 'Saniflo Sanicondens Best Pump_1559541743.jpg', '0', NULL, '2019-06-03 04:02:23', '2019-06-03 04:02:23'),
